data.chText: （铁路客车车厢分隔成的）隔间
data.enText: one of the separate sections which a coach/car on a train is divided into

data.chText: （家具或设备等的）分隔间，隔层
data.enText: one of the separate sections that sth such as a piece of furniture or equipment has for keeping things in
The desk has a secret compartment.

data.chText: 在烤箱的下面有一个便利的橱柜。
data.enText: There is a handy storage compartment beneath the oven.

means: (铁路客车车厢分隔成的)隔间

tr: a partitioned section, chamber, or separate room within a larger enclosed area
a space into which an area is subdivided

value.def: A compartment is one of the separate spaces into which a railway carriage is divided.

example.ex: On the way home we shared our first class compartment with a group of businessmen.
example.tran: 回家的路上，我们和一群生意人一起坐在一等车厢。

value.def: A compartment is one of the separate parts of an object that is used for keeping things in.

example.ex: I put a bottle of champagne in the freezer compartment.
example.tran: 我把一瓶香槟放进冷冻室。

example.ex: ...the secret compartment of my jewel box.

trans: (汽车前排座位前放小物件的)杂物箱
